00:23:20,120 --> 00:23:23,080
before kind of like side-eyeing back to you.

537
00:23:23,880 --> 00:23:24,920
So that's what you see.

538
00:23:25,480 --> 00:23:29,560
Guys, I don't know if that's going to do anything for us.

539
00:23:29,560 --> 00:23:30,040
I didn't.

540
00:23:30,920 --> 00:23:31,560
It didn't.

541
00:23:31,560 --> 00:23:33,240
It doesn't seem to speak common.

542
00:23:33,240 --> 00:23:37,880
I run through the same thing in Dwarvish, Elvish, and Gnomish.

543
00:23:38,680 --> 00:23:42,600
In that six seconds that you run through that phrase that many times,

544
00:23:43,560 --> 00:23:47,080
the same, you don't get anything more than what you've got.

545
00:23:47,080 --> 00:23:47,800
Okay.

546
00:23:47,800 --> 00:23:49,480
Shocked it doesn't speak Gnomish.

547
00:23:49,480 --> 00:23:50,520
I know, right?

548
00:23:52,040 --> 00:23:57,160
It's Follin's turn, and he's now behind the animal.

549
00:23:58,520 --> 00:24:01,960
And he is looking at you, Cav, trying to negotiate with it.

550
00:24:01,960 --> 00:24:06,680
And he's trying to signal Bonwyn with his sword.

551
00:24:08,040 --> 00:24:10,040
He's got a very good vantage point.

552
00:24:10,519 --> 00:24:14,279
He's trying to signal to you, should he take a hit?

553
00:24:15,079 --> 00:24:17,480
Oh, Coward can't even do it by himself,

554
00:24:17,480 --> 00:24:20,039
has to make Carla decide whether or not he killed the elk.

555
00:24:20,039 --> 00:24:21,559
He's going to stab it in the butt?

556
00:24:21,559 --> 00:24:22,759
He's going to stab the...

557
00:24:22,759 --> 00:24:24,680
Why are we stabbing things in the butt?

558
00:24:25,240 --> 00:24:26,759
This is why we defer to you.

559
00:24:27,960 --> 00:24:31,879
You've stabbed the most things in the butt, I think, out of everybody.

560
00:24:31,879 --> 00:24:33,639
Bit of an expert on the team.

561
00:24:33,639 --> 00:24:35,399
I mean, it's not responding.

562
00:24:35,399 --> 00:24:37,720
I shouldn't be tricked by its beauty.

563
00:24:38,120 --> 00:24:43,480
I've already damaged it, so I think I give him a nod.

564
00:24:43,480 --> 00:24:45,480
Okay, he's going to try and...

565
00:24:45,480 --> 00:24:47,720
Because it's going to attack again, and last time that happened,

566
00:24:47,720 --> 00:24:50,279
Alydin ragged all up into the air and felt like...

567
00:24:50,279 --> 00:24:52,279
And those other guys, but I don't really care about them.

568
00:24:52,279 --> 00:24:53,079
They ran away!

569
00:24:53,079 --> 00:24:54,279
But I do care about Alydin.

570
00:24:54,279 --> 00:24:56,279
Yeah, they just peaced out.

571
00:24:56,839 --> 00:25:01,640
Then he's going to take his longsword that he has,

572
00:25:02,120 --> 00:25:06,839
and as stealthily as he can, rush up behind the elk.

573
00:25:07,079 --> 00:25:12,839
And jump down and strike into it, which he succeeds on his attack.

574
00:25:13,799 --> 00:25:17,399
And that's going to be seven damage.

575
00:25:18,919 --> 00:25:20,919
It's always more upsetting when it's a mammal.

576
00:25:20,919 --> 00:25:21,720
Do you find that?

577
00:25:21,720 --> 00:25:22,359
Sure.

578
00:25:22,359 --> 00:25:23,159
100%!

579
00:25:24,599 --> 00:25:28,439
With no claws or fangs or anything like that.

580
00:25:28,439 --> 00:25:29,959
Red eyes, yeah.

581
00:25:29,959 --> 00:25:32,279
It's an animal that in nature I would be like,

582
00:25:32,279 --> 00:25:34,759
what a wonder and delight!

583
00:25:34,759 --> 00:25:38,920
He cuts down into this elk, which the antlers shake again,

584
00:25:38,920 --> 00:25:42,599
and more of this ink flies off, and there's this huge snort.

585
00:25:42,599 --> 00:25:48,599
And the elk opens its mouth, you think, to make a call,

586
00:25:49,720 --> 00:25:51,720
a yell, a scream of some sort.

587
00:25:53,079 --> 00:26:00,119
But as the sword digs into it, and its legs collapse beneath it,

588
00:26:00,600 --> 00:26:07,880
its entire body begins to dissolve into these paper fragments

589
00:26:07,880 --> 00:26:11,640
that appear to be soaked in this heavy black ink.

590
00:26:14,280 --> 00:26:18,520
Follens standing over top of it as this paper is blowing away

591
00:26:18,520 --> 00:26:21,080
in the wind and the fogs dispersing.

592
00:26:21,080 --> 00:26:27,640
And what's left are the antlers of the elk surrounded by this paper.

593
00:26:30,120 --> 00:26:37,160
Dibs.

594
00:26:37,160 --> 00:26:38,360
I know you can kill Dib, but...

595
00:26:39,000 --> 00:26:39,800
She called dibs.

596
00:26:39,800 --> 00:26:40,440
I mean, you can't...

597
00:26:41,080 --> 00:26:42,440
That's legally binding.

598
00:26:42,440 --> 00:26:44,440
That's legally binding.

599
00:26:44,440 --> 00:26:47,000
You all kind of collect yourselves,

600
00:26:47,000 --> 00:26:52,680
and Follens calls back to the men who had hightailed it back into the forest.

601
00:26:53,320 --> 00:26:54,440
They're already at them punks' death.

602
00:26:54,440 --> 00:26:58,760
They're too far to hear him, or if they have heard him,

603
00:26:58,759 --> 00:27:01,319
they're not turning around coming back at this point.

604
00:27:01,319 --> 00:27:05,400
So he looks down and he's like brushing between the papers

605
00:27:05,400 --> 00:27:06,839
as you all come to join him.

606
00:27:06,839 --> 00:27:14,440
And he says, there's two inks, there's little words more than anything.

607
00:27:14,440 --> 00:27:15,960
I don't see any phrases on this.

608
00:27:21,960 --> 00:27:23,000
What happened here?

609
00:27:23,640 --> 00:27:26,599
Well, first, you need some new adventuring buddies,

610
00:27:26,600 --> 00:27:28,680
or I hope the other ones.

611
00:27:28,680 --> 00:27:30,200
Those guys can't go with you.

612
00:27:30,200 --> 00:27:32,840
They ran at the first sign of trouble and you were here

613
00:27:32,840 --> 00:27:35,720
and you protected Alydin and kept like...

614
00:27:35,720 --> 00:27:36,840
Yeah, thanks, man.

615
00:27:36,840 --> 00:27:38,360
You're crushing it as an adventure.

616
00:27:39,160 --> 00:27:41,080
Well, thank you.

617
00:27:41,080 --> 00:27:41,800
First of all.

618
00:27:41,800 --> 00:27:42,280
Yeah, no.

619
00:27:43,720 --> 00:27:45,960
I didn't think they were going to really hold...

620
00:27:45,960 --> 00:27:50,280
I didn't expect it to charge us and throw them into the trees.

621
00:27:51,080 --> 00:27:52,760
It really wasn't an animal, it was a book.

622
00:27:53,560 --> 00:27:56,040
It was somehow a book, but also an elk?

623
00:27:57,080 --> 00:28:01,480
Was it a book about an elk and then it turned into what the book was about?

624
00:28:02,200 --> 00:28:05,000
I mean, that's not one of the five books Cav's ever read, so...

625
00:28:05,720 --> 00:28:07,080
I wish Bazaar was here.

626
00:28:07,080 --> 00:28:09,080
Oh, God, I was just thinking the same thing.

627
00:28:09,080 --> 00:28:10,920
All the magic-y shit happens when Bazaar's never here.

628
00:28:10,920 --> 00:28:14,200
All of this weird stuff is happening and Bazaar isn't here

629
00:28:14,200 --> 00:28:17,320
and he's the only one that knows about this stuff.

630
00:28:17,320 --> 00:28:21,800
I want to gather all the pages that I can, even though they're ink.

631
00:28:21,800 --> 00:28:24,120
Yeah, they're ink covered and mostly scraps.

632
00:28:24,120 --> 00:28:25,640
Yeah, but yeah, you gather what you can.

633
00:28:25,640 --> 00:28:26,440
Me as well.

634
00:28:26,600 --> 00:28:32,840
Follon looks down and there is a pool of what you can presume

635
00:28:32,840 --> 00:28:37,080
is this creature's blood in the space, but it looks like the ink.

636
00:28:37,960 --> 00:28:43,400
There are the antlers and Follon and it pulls out of his satchel and he says,

637
00:28:43,400 --> 00:28:43,720
I don't...

638
00:28:45,160 --> 00:28:47,640
He says, your friend looks into this.

639
00:28:47,640 --> 00:28:51,160
Maybe we collect some of this and maybe he can do something with it?

640
00:28:51,160 --> 00:28:51,960
Great idea.

641
00:28:51,960 --> 00:28:52,680
Thanks, Follon.

642
00:28:52,680 --> 00:28:53,180
Yeah.

643
00:28:54,060 --> 00:28:56,700
So he collects some of the ink-like substance

644
00:28:57,500 --> 00:29:01,259
and there are the antlers, which are, as you're now up to them

645
00:29:01,259 --> 00:29:03,900
and the ink has more or less been shaken off,

646
00:29:03,900 --> 00:29:08,220
they are polished antlers that shimmer faintly with the light around it.

647
00:29:08,220 --> 00:29:09,259
I'll just take these.

648
00:29:10,380 --> 00:29:11,019
I always...

649
00:29:11,019 --> 00:29:12,140
Stab them up on my shoulder.

650
00:29:12,140 --> 00:29:13,580
Okay, you okay with...

651
00:29:13,580 --> 00:29:14,779
You're good?

652
00:29:14,779 --> 00:29:15,500
Oh, yeah.

653
00:29:15,500 --> 00:29:16,460
Yeah, okay.

654
00:29:16,460 --> 00:29:17,900
This is a flesh wound.

655
00:29:17,900 --> 00:29:18,400
It's fine.

656
00:29:18,940 --> 00:29:19,500
Okay.

657
00:29:19,500 --> 00:29:21,259
Might have to get you a bigger bucket.

658
00:29:21,259 --> 00:29:22,860
Yeah, I was thinking the same thing.

659
00:29:22,940 --> 00:29:26,780
You collect everything you can for more investigation,

660
00:29:26,780 --> 00:29:29,980
both bizarre or anybody else later.

661
00:29:30,860 --> 00:29:32,780
You manage to find...

662
00:29:33,740 --> 00:29:37,820
You bring back a couple vials of the blood substance.

663
00:29:37,820 --> 00:29:41,260
You have the antlers and as you're collecting the papers,

664
00:29:41,260 --> 00:29:47,980
there is this cracked stone in the shape of a hoof

665
00:29:48,860 --> 00:29:51,500
that you find underneath a big pile.

666
00:29:51,500 --> 00:29:53,339
Pick that up and take that with you as well.

667
00:29:54,059 --> 00:29:54,539
For sure.

668
00:29:55,259 --> 00:29:57,500
Well, I mean, it's getting late,

669
00:29:57,500 --> 00:29:59,420
but we could probably still make it back.

670
00:29:59,420 --> 00:30:02,299
I don't think we necessarily need to stay in...

671
00:30:03,019 --> 00:30:03,740
We found it.

672
00:30:04,460 --> 00:30:05,740
I mean, we did find it.

673
00:30:05,740 --> 00:30:07,500
This was the goal and we did it.

674
00:30:07,500 --> 00:30:08,619
It was a lot quicker than we thought.

675
00:30:09,740 --> 00:30:11,579
I guess we can put that rumor to rest.

676
00:30:11,579 --> 00:30:14,539
It did exist.

677
00:30:14,539 --> 00:30:15,660
Did exist?

678
00:30:15,660 --> 00:30:16,220
Yeah.

679
00:30:16,220 --> 00:30:18,220
I mean, it still might, somewhere.

680
00:30:19,019 --> 00:30:21,420
Yeah, I mean, who knows what Book L...

681
00:30:21,420 --> 00:30:22,860
Paper.

682
00:30:22,860 --> 00:30:23,340
Yeah.

683
00:30:23,340 --> 00:30:25,660
He's in a little bit of shock himself.

684
00:30:25,660 --> 00:30:27,820
Everybody heads back towards town.

685
00:30:28,380 --> 00:30:33,180
As you get back to town, it's late evening

686
00:30:33,180 --> 00:30:37,980
and usually there's still a good crowd of people

687
00:30:37,980 --> 00:30:40,860
going shop to shop, restaurant hopping,

688
00:30:40,860 --> 00:30:41,580
that sort of thing.

689
00:30:43,259 --> 00:30:47,900
But you hear from the Artisan District town center

690
00:30:48,539 --> 00:30:50,539
on the Artisan District side of town.

691
00:30:51,900 --> 00:30:55,900
Comotion coming from that part of the city.

692
00:30:58,700 --> 00:31:00,300
Folan looks to you and says,

693
00:31:01,820 --> 00:31:03,900
it sounds like there's something happening over there,

694
00:31:03,900 --> 00:31:05,980
but I'm going to go see if I can find the others.

695
00:31:07,820 --> 00:31:09,019
Yeah, tear them a new one.

696
00:31:09,019 --> 00:31:10,300
Tell them thanks for nothing.

697
00:31:10,300 --> 00:31:11,340
No, of course.

698
00:31:11,340 --> 00:31:12,300
Thank you for coming with.

699
00:31:13,259 --> 00:31:13,820
Of course.

700
00:31:14,460 --> 00:31:16,620
I don't think that would have gone nearly as...

701
00:31:19,340 --> 00:31:20,539
The way it did.

702
00:31:21,180 --> 00:31:22,619
I don't think it would have been as beneficial.

703
00:31:23,180 --> 00:31:23,659
So thank you.

704
00:31:24,220 --> 00:31:24,940
Thank you again.

705
00:31:24,940 --> 00:31:29,180
He kind of bows his head and heads off.

706
00:31:29,180 --> 00:31:31,259
I guess we got to go see what's going on, right?

707
00:31:31,259 --> 00:31:32,700
Well, is there an event?

708
00:31:32,700 --> 00:31:34,059
I don't remember there being anything going on.

709
00:31:34,059 --> 00:31:36,460
I don't remember there being anything planned tonight,

710
00:31:36,460 --> 00:31:39,579
but yeah, we got to go see.

711
00:31:41,259 --> 00:31:42,619
You make your way down

712
00:31:42,619 --> 00:31:45,899
and this is in the little square outside

713
00:31:45,899 --> 00:31:47,659
of where the Brutal Awakening is.

714
00:31:47,660 --> 00:31:49,100
So there's shops around,

715
00:31:49,100 --> 00:31:51,820
but there is a large gathering of people.

716
00:31:52,779 --> 00:31:57,259
And as you're coming down the little hilled street

717
00:31:57,980 --> 00:31:59,420
that leads into the square,

718
00:32:00,380 --> 00:32:02,300
a few people look and see you

719
00:32:02,300 --> 00:32:05,900
and you can see over the top of several of their heads.

720
00:32:07,259 --> 00:32:10,940
You see that there is a crowd that's gathered around

721
00:32:10,940 --> 00:32:13,500
what looks like a lector that's been placed

722
00:32:13,500 --> 00:32:15,420
in the center of the square.

723
00:32:15,420 --> 00:32:20,380
And there is a book that somebody appears to be reading from.

724
00:32:20,380 --> 00:32:23,660
And then you hear that person yell out,

725
00:32:23,660 --> 00:32:26,380
it's not true, it can't be true.

726
00:32:26,380 --> 00:32:28,380
And they turn and they run

727
00:32:28,380 --> 00:32:30,380
and there's like an audible gasp

728
00:32:30,380 --> 00:32:32,779
as everybody looks into this book.

